<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4600605>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 6. Number of Nepticulidae species with different parameters of wingspan in the world, Holarctic, and other, mostly tropical and subtropical regions (in %) Note that species with moths distinctly in two size categories were counted for both corresponding categories, e.g., the North American Stigmella villosella (Clemens) with the wingspan range of 2.8 mm to 4.6 mm was counted twice, in the category “<4.0” and in category “4.0–4.9 mm”;" ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4600605/files/figure.png" .

